    "asOf": "2021-03-08",
    "date": "2021-05-21T12:07:40Z",
    "text": "Ending Debt Collection Harassment Act of 2021\n\nThis bill prohibits a debt collector from sending electronic communications to a consumer without the consumer's consent. The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) may not issue rules that allow a debt collector to send unlimited electronic communications. Additionally, the CFPB must report on consumer complaints about electronic communications and enforcement actions taken against debt collectors."
